  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Physician",
  "description": "<p>SingHealth Polyclinics aims to provide holistic care to optimize the delivery of healthcare outcomes for patients. We also provide opportunities for those who have keen career interests in the area of research and education. Sponsorships are also available to equip doctors with Family Medicine post-graduate qualifications. If you aspire to provide quality care to patients and help define Tomorrow's Medicine, abundant exciting challenges await you right here at SingHealth Polyclinics!</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>You can be considered for a position in any of our 10 polyclinics to provide primary care, which includes managing acute and chronic medical conditions, and providing preventive care and medical care for women and children.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Selected candidates will be offered a position commensurate with their relevant experiences, credentials and qualifications. Experienced doctors in Family Medicine can expect a competitive remuneration package commensurate with higher responsibilities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Job requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess basic medical degree registrable with the Singapore Medical Council. Oversee trained doctors with medical qualification registrable with Singapore Medical Council are welcome to apply.</li>\n  <li>Possess relevant clinical knowledge and skills in managing patients at the primary care level</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of experience as Medical Officer or equivalent</li>\n</ul>",
